dia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.017488521266271e-60, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 37-year-old and Dan Evans have won all three of their doubles clashes so far, making the quarter-finals of the competition in the process.\", \"from\": 410, \"to\": 552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 430, \"end\": 439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Die_Warzau\", \"score\": 0.9039634156816415, \"rank\": 0.10623945908900023, \"text\": \"Dan Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Die_Warzau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Die_Warzau\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Victory tonight will see the duo close in on Olympic gold, something that seemed highly unlikely just weeks ago.Murray and Evans are scheduled to face Tommy Paul and Taylor Fritz later today, with Team USA out to ruin his farewell party.Paris Olympics chiefs are unlikely to bend their rules for Andy Murray this summer|PARecently, at Wimbledon, Murray was given a special send-off.Having won the tournament twice, in 2013 and 2016 respectively, everybody came together at SW19 to celebrate an icon of British sport after he'd lost in the doubles alongside Jamie Murray.When it comes to the Olympics, however, that's unlikely to be the case.The games do not typically perform such gestures, regardless of how big the name is.\", \"from\": 554, \"to\": 1279, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 677, \"end\": 682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\", \"score\": 0.9066698021233902, \"rank\": 0.10293736226560937, \"text\": \"Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\"}, {\"begin\": 705, \"e